                                         JOHANNESBURG - Vicki Momberg has been found guilty of four counts of crimen injuria. She was charged after video footage emerged of her insulting black police officers after a smash and grab last year using the k-word. WATCH: Racist rant caught on camera.  Momberg had argued that she was traumatised following a crime and was not aware of her language when she used the k-word. However, the court has dismissed her claim and has instead convicted her of crimen injuria. The Randburg Magistrates Court has found that Momberg knew her actions were unlawful when she racially attacked black police officers.